OL,6,FA forensic post-mortem examination
OL,7,Fconcluded that although it was likely
OL,8,Fthe assault had played a role in Ms
OL,9,FAdams' death, it was not possible to
OL,10,Fexclude the possibility that death
OL,11,Fwould have occurred due to the
OL,12,Fcombined effects of cocaine use and an
OL,13,Funderlying medical condition in the
OL,14,Fabsence of an assault.
OL,16,FThis saw Loder charged with grievous
OL,17,Fbodily harm, which she pleaded guilty
OL,18,Fto.
